   <text>
      <body>
         <pb n="1r" facs="lf_vDeshmukh_1693_01.jpg"/>
         <div xml:id="orig_div1" xml:lang="per" type="endorsements" rend="top right">
            <p><lb rend="empty"/><stamp type="seal"><mentioned>
                     <persName ref="#ghulamMuhiuddin">غلام محی الدین</persName>
                      قاضی خادم شرع
                     <unclear>متین</unclear>
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">
                        <num>۱۱۹۶</num>
                     </date>
                  </mentioned></stamp>
              <lb rend="empty"/>
            <lb rend="empty"/><stamp type="seal"><mentioned>
                     <unclear>
                        <persName ref="#ghulamMuhiuddin">غلام محی الدین</persName>
                     </unclear>
                      قاضی خادم شرع متین
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">
                        <num>۱۱۹۶</num>
                     </date>
                  </mentioned></stamp>
               <lb rend="empty"/>مطابق اصل است </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div1" corresp="#orig_div1">
            <p><lb rend="empty"/>
               <stamp type="seal">round black ink seal<mentioned>
                     <persName ref="#ghulamMuhiuddin">Ghulam Muhiuddin</persName>, <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_qazi">qazi</ref>, servant of the
                     <unclear>firm</unclear>
                      law
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">1196</date>
                  <note>This date is the year the seal was issued and corresponds to 1781–82 CE. This
                        suggests that the document was copied in the last quarter of the
                        eighteenth century.</note>
                  </mentioned></stamp>
            <lb rend="empty"/>
            <lb rend="empty"/>
            <stamp type="seal">round black ink seal<mentioned>
                     <unclear>
                        <persName ref="#ghulamMuhiuddin">Ghulam Muhiuddin</persName>
                     </unclear>, <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_qazi">qazi</ref>, servant of the firm law
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">1196</date>
                  </mentioned></stamp>
               <note>It appears that there are two impressions of the same seal on the
                  document.</note>
               <lb rend="empty"/>[It] conforms to the original.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div2" xml:lang="per" type="maintext">
            <p>
               <lb/>نقل
               <lb/>پروانه بمهر
               <persName ref="#abdurrazzaqKhan">عبد الرزاق خان</persName>
                متصدیان مهمات حال و استقبال و زمینداران و مقدمان
               <lb/>مزارعان جمهور سکنه پرگنه
               <placeName ref="#kondvi">کوندوی</placeName>
                معموله
               <placeName ref="#raigarh">اسلامگده</placeName>
                عرف راهیری بدانند که
               <persName ref="#lodiKhan">لودی خان</persName>
                ولد اسمعیل
               <lb/>و
               <persName ref="#hasan">احسن</persName><note>The scribe has likely made an error here, writing Ahsan instead of Hasan. The name Hasan is given in <ref type="document" target="lf_vDeshmukh_1690_02">1690 Order of Fath Jang Khan granting the office of deshmukhi and 8 villages to the landlords Lodi and Hasan</ref>.</note>
                ولد محمد زمینداران پرگنه مذکور
               <unclear>برهبری</unclear>
                طالع در فوج فیروزی بخدمات حاضر و سرگرم مصدر
               <lb/>ترددات گردیدند لهذا خدمت دیشموکهی پرگنه مزبور و انعام موضع
               <placeName ref="#tudil">تودل</placeName>
                وغیره چهار دهه ازبابت دیشموکهی
               <lb/>و ادهیکاری و مقدمی و کشت کامتی و
               <unclear>سیته گری</unclear>
                و
               <unclear>چودهرگری</unclear>
                و
               <unclear>یپتلکی گری</unclear>
                و بیسوا و موضع
               <placeName ref="#natondi">ناتوندی</placeName>
               <lb/><unclear>بنابر</unclear>
               دیسپاندیه گری بموجب قدیم و انعام جدید و موضع
               <placeName ref="#valote">ولوته</placeName>
                وغیره سه
                <num>۳</num> 
                دهه بموجب سند بمهر
               <persName ref="#fathJangKhan">فتح جنگ خان</persName>
               <lb/>مرحوم حسب الضمن بدستور سابق بحال و مقرر
               <app><rdg cert="low">کرده</rdg><rdg cert="low">نموده</rdg></app>
               شد باید که خدمات ماموره با انعامات مزکور
               <lb/>بمشارالهما تا باولاد پیشین مقرر شناسند و 
               <unclear>سبیل</unclear>
               مومی الهما انکه بحسن سلوک خود ها
                <unclear>رعایا</unclear>
               <gap></gap>
               <lb/><unclear>باو</unclear><note>In comparison with the related document, this may be اباد</note>
               داشته در افزونی زراعت کوشیده
               <unclear>مالواجب و حقوق دیوانی موافق ضابطه</unclear>
               <lb/>
               <gap/>
               <lb/> نورزند
               <unclear>مبلغ</unclear>
               شرح ضمن انکه انعام از بابت خدمات دیشموکهی وغیره بموجب
               <gap/>
               <lb/>قدیم و انعامات حال بموجب سند
               <persName ref="#fathJangKhan">فتح جنگ خان</persName>
                و
               <persName ref="#aqaAliKhan">اقا علی خان</persName>
                مقرر شناسند </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div2" corresp="#orig_div2">
            <p>
               <lb/>Copy
               <lb/>A <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_parvana">parvana</ref> under the seal of
               <persName ref="#abdurrazzaqKhan">Abdurrazzaq Khan</persName>. Let the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mutasaddi">mutasaddis</ref> of present
               and future affairs and the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_zamindar">zamindars</ref>
               and the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_muqaddam">muqqadams</ref>
               <lb/>and the population of cultivators of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana"
                  >pargana</ref>
               <placeName ref="#kondvi">Kondvi</placeName>, under the administration of
               <placeName ref="#raigarh">Islamgarh [Raigarh]</placeName>, called Raheri, know that
               <persName ref="#lodiKhan">Lodi Khan</persName>
                son of Ismail
               <lb/>and
               <persName ref="#hasan">Hasan</persName>
                son of Muhammad, <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_zamindar">zamindars</ref> of the
               aforementioned <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> have been
               present and diligently engaged in the service of the glorious army by [providing] fortunate guidance
               <lb/>[and] embraced undertaking exertions. For this reason, they are granted the service of <ref
                  type="glossary" target="#gl_deshmukhi">deshmukhi</ref> of the aforementioned <ref
                  type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> and the <ref type="glossary"
                  target="#gl_inam">inʿam</ref> of village
               <placeName ref="#tudil">Tudil</placeName>, etc., four villages on account of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_deshmukhi"
                  >deshmukhi</ref>
               <lb/>and <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_adhikari">adhikari</ref>
               and <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_muqaddami">muqaddami</ref> and <unclear><ref
                  type="glossary" target="#gl_kashtkamati">kasht-kamati</ref> and <ref
                  type="glossary" target="#gl_sethgiri">seth-giri</ref> and <ref
                  type="glossary" target="#gl_chaudhrgiri">chaudhri-giri</ref> and <ref
                  type="glossary" target="#gl_patilkigiri">patilki-giri</ref></unclear>; and
               <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_biswa">biswa</ref>
                and the village of
               <placeName ref="#natondi">Natondi</placeName>
               <lb/>on account of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_deshpande-giri"
                  >deshpande-giri</ref> according to old [tradition] and for the new <ref
                  type="glossary" target="#gl_inam">inʿam</ref>; and the village of
               <placeName ref="#valote">Valote</placeName>, etc., three villages in accordance with the <ref type="glossary"
                  target="#gl_sanad">sanad</ref> sealed by
               <persName ref="#fathJangKhan">Fath Jang Khan</persName>,
               <lb/>deceased, in accordance with the details on the <ref type="glossary"
                  target="#gl_zimn">zimn</ref> [and] old custom. It is necessary that the services
               described with the aforementioned <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_inam"
                  >inʿams</ref>
               <lb/>be considered as settled on the two [grantees] together with their future
               descendants. The undertaking of the grantees is: they should <unclear>please the farmers</unclear>
               with their good conduct
               <lb/>and make efforts for the increase of cultivation
                <unclear>so that the assessed taxes and the assessed dues</unclear>
               <gap/>
               <lb/>
               <gap/>
               <lb/><gap></gap>The <unclear>amount</unclear> detailed in the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_zimn">zimn</ref> [is] to the effect
               [that] the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_inam">inʿam</ref> on account of the <ref
                  type="glossary" target="#gl_deshmukh">deshmukh's</ref> services, etc., due to
               <lb/>old <gap></gap>and the present <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_inam">inʿams</ref> in
               accordance with the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_sanad">sanad</ref> of
               <persName ref="#fathJangKhan">Fath Jang Khan</persName>
                and
               <persName ref="#aqaAliKhan">Aqa Ali Khan</persName>
                they shall understand as settled.</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div3" xml:lang="per" type="particulars" rend="bottom">
            <p>
               <list>
                  <lb/>
                  <head>شرح موضع</head>
                  <lb rend="empty"/>
                  <lb/>
                  <label>انعام از بابت دیشموکهی وغیره دروبست
                     <g ref="#siyaq">۴</g>
                      موضع</label>
                  <item>
                     <list>
                        <lb/>
                        <item>قریت
                           <placeName ref="#tudil">تودل</placeName>
                            یکموضع</item>
                        <lb/>
                        <item>قریت
                           <placeName ref="#wakan">واکن</placeName>
                            یکموضع</item>
                        <lb/>
                        <item>قریت
                           <unclear>
                              <placeName ref="#karijari">کریجاری</placeName>
                           </unclear>
                            یکموضع</item>
                        <lb/>
                        <item>قریت
                           <placeName ref="#ravdhal">راودهل</placeName>
                            یکموضع</item>
                     </list></item>
                  <lb rend="empty"/>
                  <lb/>
                  <label>در بابت انعام دیشپاندیه گیری
                     <gap/>
                      موضع </label>
                  <item><list>
                     <lb/>
                        <item>
                           <placeName ref="#natondi">ناتوندی</placeName>
                            یکموضع</item>
                     </list></item>
                  <lb rend="empty"/>
                  <lb/>
                  <label>و انعام بموجب سند
                     <persName ref="#aqaAliKhan">اقا علیخان</persName>
                      بر حسن تردد مورچال
                      <placeName ref="#pachor">پاچور</placeName>
                      بوقت بودند
                      <unclear>فوج</unclear>
                      امارت مرتبت
                     <persName ref="#zulfiqarKhan">ذوالفقار خان</persName>
                     بهادر
                     <g ref="#siyaq">۳</g>
                      موضع</label>
                  <item><list>
                     <lb/>
                        <item>قریت
                           <placeName ref="#valote">ولوته</placeName>
                            یکموضع</item>
                     <lb/>
                        <item>قریت
                           <unclear><placeName ref="#tamhane">تامهنه</placeName></unclear>
                            یکموضع</item>
                     <lb/>
                        <item>قریت
                           <placeName ref="#kotwalBuzurg">کوتوال بزورگ</placeName>
                        </item>
                     <lb/>
                        <item>سی دهه</item>
                     </list></item>
               </list>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div3" corresp="#orig_div3">
            <p>
               <list>
                  <lb/>
                  <head>Village Description</head>
                  <lb rend="empty"/>
                  <lb/>
                  <label><ref type="glossary" target="#gl_inam">Inʿam</ref> from the <ref
                        type="glossary" target="#gl_deshmukh">deshmukh’s</ref> account, etc.,
                     entirety of
                     <g ref="#siyaq">4</g>
                      villages</label>
                  <item>
                     <list>
                        <lb/>
                        <item>village
                           <placeName ref="#tudil">Tudil</placeName>
                            one <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mauza">mauzaʿ</ref>
                           <note>Both <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mauza">mauzaʿ</ref> and
                              qiryat mean village, but here the former is used to specify the
                              revenue unit and the latter is used as a label or 'counting
                              word.'</note>
                        </item>
                        <lb/>
                        <item>village
                           <placeName ref="#wakan">Wakan</placeName>
                            one <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mauza">mauzaʿ</ref></item>
                        <lb/>
                        <item>village
                           <unclear>
                              <placeName ref="#karijari">Karijari</placeName>
                           </unclear>
                            one <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mauza">mauzaʿ</ref></item>
                        <lb/>
                        <item>village
                           <placeName ref="#ravdhal">Ravdhal</placeName>
                            one <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mauza">mauzaʿ</ref></item>
                     </list></item>
                  <lb rend="empty"/>
                  <lb/>
                  <label>On account of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_inam">inʿam</ref> of
                        <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_deshpandegiri">deshpandegiri</ref>
                     <gap/>
                      village</label>
                  <item><list>
                     <lb/>
                        <item>
                           <placeName ref="#natondi">Natondi</placeName>
                            one <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mauza">mauzaʿ</ref></item>
                     </list></item>
                  <lb rend="empty"/>
                  <lb/>
                  <label>and the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_inam">inʿam</ref> in accordance
                     with the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_sanad">sanad</ref> of
                     <persName ref="#aqaAliKhan">Aqa Ali Khan</persName> for at the time of being [in] the army of the
                      Dignified Office of
                     <persName ref="#zulfiqarKhan">Zulfiqar Khan</persName>
                      Bahadur
                     <g ref="#siyaq">3</g>
                      villages</label>
                  <item><list>
                     <lb/>
                        <item>village
                           <placeName ref="#valote">Valote</placeName>
                            one <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mauza">mauzaʿ</ref></item>
                     <lb/>
                        <item>village
                           <unclear>
                              <placeName ref="#tamhane">Tamhane</placeName>
                           </unclear><note>This is presumably the same village spelled as Tamana in the 1690 document <ref type="document" target="lf_vDeshmukh_1690_02">Order of Fath Jang Khan granting the office of deshmukhi and 8 villages to the landlords Lodi and Hasan</ref>.</note>
                            one <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mauza">mauzaʿ</ref></item>
                     <lb/>
                        <item>village
                           <placeName ref="#kotwalBuzurg">Kotwal Buzurg</placeName>
                        </item>
                     <lb/>
                        <item>Three<note>The scribe wrote thirty, but from context this is an error for three.</note> villages</item>
                     </list></item>
               </list></p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div4" xml:lang="per" type="maintext" rend="bottom">
            <p>
                فی التاریخ
               <date calendar="#julus">چهاردهم
                  <num>۱۴</num>
                   شهر ذی قعده سنه
                  <num>۳۷</num>
               </date>
                از جلوس منعمت مایوس
               <note>this is likely an error for مانوس</note>
                قلمی شد 
               <g ref="#baiz">بیضه</g> </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div4" corresp="#orig_div4">
            <p>Written on the
               <date calendar="#julus">14th of Zi qaʿdah 37 years</date>
                from the enthronement. <g ref="#baiz">Ended</g>.
               <note>There is probably an abjad word play in this line.</note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
